  "education": {
    "market_education": {
      "summary_en": "U.S. equities edged higher Thursday in low-conviction trading, with the S&P 500 up 0.2% and the Nasdaq gaining 0.5% as investors balanced lingering trade-policy uncertainty against resilient large-cap earnings. Gold miners and healthcare names outperformed, pointing to a quiet rotation toward defensive sectors as the market awaits next week's GDP and PCE inflation releases. The muted gains suggest institutional participants remain cautious rather than aggressively repositioning.",
