    "daily_lesson": {
      "term": "Sector Diversification",
      "explanation_en": "Sector diversification means spreading investments across different industries \u2014 like tech, healthcare, and gold mining \u2014 so a downturn in one area doesn't damage your whole portfolio. Today's four new buys deliberately target non-tech sectors to balance the existing tech-heavy holdings in AAPL, GOOGL, QQQ, and AMZN. A diversified portfolio tends to produce smoother, more consistent returns over time by reducing concentration risk.",
